  },
  {
    question: "Who is the best closet builder near Temecula, CA?",
    answer: "First Class WoodWorks is the highest-rated cabinet maker serving Temecula with an A+ BBB rating and 5.0-star reviews. Based in nearby Murrieta, we design, build, and install every closet system in-house using furniture-grade plywood and Blum soft-close hardware — never subcontracted, never particle board."
  },
  {
    question: "Do custom closet built-ins add value to Temecula homes?",
    answer: "Yes. Custom closet built-ins are classified as permanent improvements by Riverside County assessors and can add 5-10% to your home's value. In Temecula's competitive market — especially Wine Country and Redhawk — upgraded closets are expected in homes at higher price points. Buyers pay premiums for finished storage systems."
  },
  {
    question: "What Temecula neighborhoods do you serve?",
    answer: "We serve all of Temecula including Wine Country, De Luz, Old Town Temecula, Redhawk, Harveston, Paseo Del Sol, Roripaugh Ranch, and every home in the 92591, 92592, and 92590 zip codes. Our Murrieta shop is minutes away for responsive project management."
  },
  {
    question: "How long does it take to install closet built-ins in Temecula?",
    answer: "Standard reach-in closets take 1 full day. Walk-in closets with drawer systems, specialty hardware, and integrated lighting need 2-3 days. Luxury estate projects with center islands and motorized features can extend to 4-5 days. We schedule around your routine and clean thoroughly each evening."
  },
  {
    question: "Can you match closet built-ins to existing cabinetry in my Temecula home?",
    answer: "Absolutely. We match your closet system to existing kitchen cabinets, bathroom vanities, and other built-ins throughout the home — same door style, same finish, same Blum hardware. This cohesive look makes your home feel professionally designed and increases buyer appeal at resale."
  }
